00:05:50.740 --> 00:05:55.310
Now onto animals. American animals, like llamas
and guinea pigs, never really caught on in

00:05:55.310 --> 00:06:00.590
Eurasia. But imports to the Americas, like
pigs, cows and horses were revolutionary.

00:06:00.590 --> 00:06:01.840
Let's go to the thought bubble:

00:06:01.840 --> 00:06:06.420
First of all, these animals, especially pigs,
completely remade the food supply. Pigs breed

00:06:06.430 --> 00:06:11.370
really quickly, they eat anything and they
turn into bacon, which made them heroes to

00:06:11.370 --> 00:06:15.830
the new world just as today they are heroes
to the internet. Here's how quickly pigs breed:

00:06:15.830 --> 00:06:21.759
When Hernando de Soto arrived in Florida in
1539, he brought 13 pigs. By the time of his

00:06:21.759 --> 00:06:27.340
death, there were 700 - that was 3 years later.
The abundance of meat and plentiful land for

00:06:27.340 --> 00:06:32.210
agriculture and grazing meant that Europeans
in the Americas very rarely experienced famine,

00:06:32.210 --> 00:06:35.840
and despite what you may have learned about
religious and political freedom, the main

00:06:35.840 --> 00:06:39.650
reason Europeans came to America was to eat.

00:06:39.650 --> 00:06:43.319
Large European animals also changed the nature
of work in the Americas. Before Europeans,

00:06:43.319 --> 00:06:47.840
the largest beast of burden was the llama,
and at best it could carry like, 100 lbs.

00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:52.569
This meant that for the long distance travel
that the Inca engaged in, the primary transportation

00:06:52.569 --> 00:06:57.770
animal was Incas. Oxen, when combined with
their plows, made it possible to bring more

00:06:57.770 --> 00:07:02.879
land under cultivation and also made transportation
easier and more efficient, and plus European

00:07:02.879 --> 00:07:04.639
animals remade culture.

00:07:04.639 --> 00:07:09.060
The grossly stereotypical American Indian,
like from the movies, riding the Great Plains

00:07:09.060 --> 00:07:14.099
with an eagle feather headdress and war paint,
well he didn't exist before the Columbian

00:07:14.099 --> 00:07:17.990
Exchange because there were no horses for
him to ride. And the introduction of horses

00:07:17.990 --> 00:07:22.539
allowed many Native Americans to abandon agriculture
in favor of a nomadic lifestyle because riding

00:07:22.539 --> 00:07:26.960
around hunting buffalo made them far richer
than farming ever had. Thanks Thought Bubble.

00:07:26.960 --> 00:07:31.340
While animals and diseases completely reshaped
the New World, it was New World plants that

00:07:31.340 --> 00:07:33.030
had the biggest effect on Eurasia.

00:07:33.030 --> 00:07:37.060
Sure, Europeans brought over some crops that
we now grow here in the Americas like wheat

00:07:37.060 --> 00:07:41.259
and grapes, both of which are necessary for
Catholic mass, but New World plants radically

00:07:41.259 --> 00:07:46.620
changed the lives of millions, maybe hundreds
of millions of Africans, Asians and Europeans,

00:07:46.620 --> 00:07:49.199
specifically by making pizza possible.

00:07:49.199 --> 00:07:55.289
[Heavenly singing, "It was the greatest gift
of all."]

